body.description: Fabricated from high-quality stainless steel, the single-piece, precision-stamped blades boast excellent cutting precision.The professional, satin-polished, fine-edge blades are finely honed for long-lasting precision. The knives' full tang construction and ergonomic handles give you the balance and strength you need to confidently slice through tough cuts with ease. Easy to use, these dishwasher-safe knives are also easy to maintain.Henckels makes essential kitchen knives that every home chef needs. Each knife offers high quality at an exceptional value. Created in 1895 by Zwilling J.A. Henckels, this value-driven brand guarantees the same durability, design and ease of use for which the global company is known. Equip your kitchen with expertise with Henckels.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great brand and great product
reviews.reviewText: Gave as a gift and they love them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great price through Amazon - plus these knives can be place din a dishwasher. Henkel's is an amazing brand, sharp quality knives. As part of the solutions series you can add other knives and create a set you will have for years.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent quality knife set.
reviews.reviewText: I am not a paid reviewer.Excellent quality knife set. Dishwasher safe. Sharp blades that cur without issue. These knives make quick work of food prep.I am a fan of the quality workmanship that Henckels provides with its knives and cookware; it makes my life easier and their price points are attractive.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good, not great.
reviews.reviewText: Over all this isn’t a bad deal, it’s a decent knife you can sharpen at a dencent price. While this may be a Henkels set, it is definitely their value brand. The tangs and the blades are much thinner than their more expensive lines, maybe by half. The blades are very flexible and it’s a noticeable difference from the more expensive stuff. If you just want a decent knife that you can sharpen and look good, this is fine. If you’re looking for sturdier, more substantial knives, spend the money to get something better.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best Knives I’ve Ever Used
reviews.reviewText: I have used lots of knives, including Cutco knives which cost lots more because of their business model and do not hold an edge. These Henckels knives are terrific! They are well-balanced, sharp and such a pleasure to use. I make lots of dishes requiring chopping, dicing, and mincing and I get meals prepared quickly with these knives. This starter set has the essential knives you need. The serrated knife cuts bread better than any bread knife I have used. I consider these an excellent buy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars sharp value for money
reviews.reviewText: Bought these to make my parents' cooking easier. Knives are sharp, parents are happy. Great success. Would buy again, except these will last a very very long time, no need. Excellent quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Henckel name on super cheap knives
reviews.reviewText: Boy, I have had Henckel knives my whole life and these don't resemble them a bit. They are a poor knock off with the Henckel name. Made in India, thin blade, just not even close to the quality I am familiar with.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The 7" knife is perfect for my little hands.
reviews.reviewText: I have a whole set of Henkel knives. The mistake I made when I purchased them was that I should not have bought the serrated knives. My daughter has the plain unserrated knives that I think still remain sharp for a long time.
I appreciate the quality, sharpness and warranty.
Love these knives so sharp, didn’t realize how dull my knives were till these came.

I didn't realize how bad my old set was until I got this set. I cut my finger on the first use. Be careful. These knives are beautiful and very, very sharp (as a kitchen knife should be). I love them.

These were a replacement for my 20-year-old knives. They work very well, and are as sharp and functional as it says in the description.The 3 sizes are great for someone who doesn't do a lot of fancy cooking, but needs decent knives when they do.I also bought 3 knife sheaths that fit perfectly, and will protect the knives (and my fingers) when they're in the drawer.
Great set of knives & extremely sharp. Very good value.
